Package: cl-xmls
Version: 1.2
Revision: 1
Description: Simple XML parser for Common Lisp
License: BSD
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: cl

Depends: clc, clisp-clc | cmucl-clc | openmcl-clc | sbcl-clc

Source: http://common-lisp.net/project/xmls/xmls-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: f67e68b05a75f47474868f92cd4d2b0a
SourceDirectory: xmls-%v

CompileScript: <<
  chmod 644 *.lisp
  chmod 644 *.asd
<<

InstallScript: <<
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/source/xmls
  cp -Rp * %i/share/common-lisp/source/xmls
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/systems
  ln -s %p/share/common-lisp/source/xmls/xmls.asd %i/share/common-lisp/systems/xmls.asd
<<

PostInstScript: %p/sbin/register-common-lisp-source xmls
PreRmScript: %p/sbin/unregister-common-lisp-source xmls


DocFiles: ChangeLog COPYING README.html

DescDetail: <<
Xmls is a small, simple, non-validating xml parser for Common Lisp.
It's designed to be a self-contained, easily embedded parser that
recognizes a useful subset of the XML spec.  It provides a simple
mapping from xml to lisp s-expressions and back.
<<

DescUsage: <<
(require "asdf")
(require "xmls")
<<

Homepage: http://common-lisp.net/project/xmls/

